<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
1.1. 
<taxonomicName LSID="F11DF794-F5CE-5749-ABB9-3D175FC578BB" authority="(A. G. Schulz) M. Pell. &amp; C. N. Horn" authorityName="Pellegrini &amp; Horn &amp; Almeida" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="A. G. Schulz" class="Liliopsida" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="Pontederia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pontederia meyeri" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="meyeri" status="comb. nov.">Pontederia meyeri (A.G.Schulz) M.Pell. &amp; C.N.Horn</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="0" pageNumber="25">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. G. Schulz" authorityYear="1942" class="Liliopsida" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="Eichhornia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eichhornia meyeri" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="meyeri">Eichhornia meyeri</taxonomicName>
A.G.Schulz, Darwiniana 6: 56. 1942. Lectotype (designated here). ARGENTINA. Chaco, Cote Lai, 25 June 1939, fl., fr., 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">T. Meyer 2640</emphasis>
(SI barcode SI000621!; isolectotypes: GH barcode GH00057534!, LIL barcode LIL000196!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
Restricted to Argentina, Paraguay and Brazil (states of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ceará">Ceara</normalizedToken>
, Mato Grosso and Mato Grosso do Sul).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="nomenclatural notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Nomenclatural notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
<bibRefCitation author="Schulz, AG" journalOrPublisher="Darwiniana" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" pagination="45 - 87" refId="B95" refString="Schulz, AG, 1942. Las Pontederiaceas de la Argentina. Darwiniana 6 (1): 45 - 87" title="Las Pontederiaceas de la Argentina." volume="6" year="1942">Schulz (1942)</bibRefCitation>
, when describing his new 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="E." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. meyeri" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="meyeri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">E. meyeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, cites two specimens from the same collection, one housed at SI and another at GH. Furthermore, a third specimen, housed at LIL was found by us. After carefully analysing the syntypes, we noticed that the specimen at SI perfectly matches the original illustration. Furthermore, it is widely known that Schulz worked at the Instituto de 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Botánica">Botanica</normalizedToken>
Darwinion, thus, making the specimen at SI the obvious choice of a lectotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="taxonomical notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Taxonomical notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
Current databases (
<bibRefCitation author="eMonocot" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" publicationUrl="http://e-monocot.org" refId="B29" refString="eMonocot, 2010. eMonocot (Version 1.0.2). http://e-monocot.org" title="eMonocot (Version 1.0.2)." url="http://e-monocot.org" year="2010">eMonocot 2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="The Plant List" journalOrPublisher="Mathematical Biosciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" publicationUrl="http://www.theplantlist.org" refId="B114" refString="The Plant List, 2013. The Plant List (Version 1.1). http://www.theplantlist.org" title="The Plant List (Version 1.1)." url="http://www.theplantlist.org" year="2013">The Plant List 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Govaerts, R" journalOrPublisher="Hindasia Publishers, Delhi" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" publicationUrl="http://wcsp.science.kew.org/" refId="B40" refString="Govaerts, R, 2018. World Checklist of Pontederiaceae. Facilitated by the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew. http://wcsp.science.kew.org/" title="World Checklist of Pontederiaceae. Facilitated by the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew." url="http://wcsp.science.kew.org/" year="2018">Govaerts 2018</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tropicos. org" journalOrPublisher="Mathematical Biosciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" publicationUrl="http://www.tropicos.org/" refId="B116" refString="Tropicos.org, 2018. Tropicos. Missouri Botanical Garden. http://www.tropicos.org/" title="Tropicos. Missouri Botanical Garden." url="http://www.tropicos.org/" year="2018">Tropicos.org 2018</bibRefCitation>
) have treated 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="E." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. meyeri" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="meyeri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">E. meyeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(≡ 
<taxonomicName family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. meyeri" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="meyeri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. meyeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="E." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. paniculata" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="paniculata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">E. paniculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(≡ 
<taxonomicName family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. paniculata" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="paniculata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. paniculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Nonetheless, as indicated in our identification key and by 
<bibRefCitation author="Horn, CN" journalOrPublisher="Candollea" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" pagination="127 - 130" refId="B55" refString="Horn, CN, 1998. Notulae ad Floram Paraguaiensem 66: A note on Eichhornia paniculata (Spreng.) Solms and Eichhornia meyeri A.G.Schulz (Pontederiaceae) in Paraguay. Candollea 53: 127 - 130" title="Notulae ad Floram Paraguaiensem 66: A note on Eichhornia paniculata (Spreng.) Solms and Eichhornia meyeri A. G. Schulz (Pontederiaceae) in Paraguay." volume="53" year="1998">Horn (1998)</bibRefCitation>
, both species are distinct, being easily differentiated in the field and herbaria. Thus, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="E." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. meyeri" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="meyeri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">E. meyeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here re-established and transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="subg. Cabanisia (Klotzsch ex Schltdl.) M. Pell. &amp; C. N. Horn" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="subg. Cabanisia (Klotzsch ex Schltdl.) M. Pell. &amp; C. N. Horn" baseAuthorityYear="2018" class="Liliopsida" family="Commelinaceae" genus="Pontederia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pontederia" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Pontederia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">s.l.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
